{"title_page": "COVID-19 pandemic in Mauritius", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Mauritius}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = COVID-19 pandemic in Mauritius\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mauritius.svg\n| legend1         = Map of the COVID-19 outbreak in Mauritius\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Mauritius]]\n| first_case      = Camp de Masque Pave\n| arrival_date    = 21 February 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day=21|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 314\n| deaths          = 10\n| confirmed_cases = 332<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.covid19.mu/ |title=Covid19 {{!}} Ministry of Health and Wellness |website=covid19|access-date=2 May 2020}}</ref>\n| active_cases    = 5<ref group=Note>Exclude three patients who left Mauritius on 13 April 2020.</ref><ref name=\"thre\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-72-autres-patients-gueris-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 72 autres patients gu\u00e9ris \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=18 April 2020|access-date=30 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"thyu\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-312-patients-maurice-gueris-jusquici|title=Covid-19 : 312 patients \u00e0 Maurice gu\u00e9ris jusqu\u2019ici|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=1 May 2020|access-date=1 May 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|http://www.covid19.mu/}}<br>{{URL|https://besafemoris.mu/}}\n}}\n\nThe [[COVID-19 pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Mauritius]] in March 2020. Since the first three cases of [[COVID-19|Covid-19]] were confirmed, the Mauritian authorities have been conducting 'Contact tracing': people who have been in contact with infected patients have been placed under quarantine, including doctors, nurses and police officers.<ref name=\"Zero\"/><ref name=\"ghy\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-policier-proche-de-la-patiente-de-20-ans-en-quarantaine|title=Covid-19 : un policier, proche de la patiente de 20 ans, en quarantaine|date=28 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328212943/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-policier-proche-de-la-patiente-de-20-ans-en-quarantaine|archive-date=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"gdj\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-40-membres-du-personnel-soignant-en-quarantaine|title=Covid-19 : 40 membres du personnel soignant en quarantaine|date=27 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328211803/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-40-membres-du-personnel-soignant-en-quarantaine|archive-date=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> No cases have been reported in [[Rodrigues]], [[Agal\u00e9ga]] and [[St. Brandon]].<ref name=\"nineteen\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-rodrigues-aucun-cas-positif-157-personnes-en-quarantaine|title=COVID-19 - Rodrigues : Aucun cas positif, 157 personnes en quarantaine|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=2 April 2020|access-date=4 April 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404142018/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-rodrigues-aucun-cas-positif-157-personnes-en-quarantaine|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"agale\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for Covid-19 has been much lower than that of [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n\n=== March 2020 ===\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic sidebar|expanded=locations}}\n* On 18 March 2020, the [[Prime Minister of Mauritius|Prime Minister]] [[Pravind Jugnauth]] confirmed that there were three cases of Covid-19 in Mauritius.<ref name=\"First\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-trois-cas-positifs-au-covid-19-maurice |title=[Breaking News] Trois cas positifs au Covid-19 \u00e0 Maurice |date=18 March 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]] |language=fr |access-date=19 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320135748/https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-trois-cas-positifs-au-covid-19-maurice |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* On 19 March 2020, the Prime Minister announced that the country would be under \"sanitary\" lockdown for two weeks as from 6:00 AM on 20 March 2020. During the lockdown, only the essential services (police, hospitals, dispensaries, private clinics, firefighters) and certain economic activities (shops, banks, supermarkets, bakeries, pharmacies) and minimum public transport service would operate.<ref name=\"Fifth\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-covid-19-pravind-jugnauth-annonce-un-confinement-total|title=[Breaking News] Covid-19 : Pravind Jugnauth annonce un confinement total|date=19 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319181127/https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-covid-19-pravind-jugnauth-annonce-un-confinement-total|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The Mauritian government received the help of several hotels around the island, as at 19 March 2020, at least 1700 hotel rooms had been provided to place people under quarantine.<ref name=\"Hotel\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/solidarite-les-hotels-mettent-1-700-chambres-la-disposition-de-la-sante|title=Solidarit\u00e9 : les h\u00f4tels mettent 1 700 chambres \u00e0 la disposition de la Sant\u00e9\n|date=23 March 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"Hotel2\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-groupe-beachcomber-met-lhotel-victoria-beachcomber-la-disposition-de-letat|title=Covid-19 : Le Groupe Beachcomber met l'h\u00f4tel Victoria Beachcomber \u00e0 la disposition de l'Etat|date=21 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322163222/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-groupe-beachcomber-met-lhotel-victoria-beachcomber-la-disposition-de-letat|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On the same day, an incident was reported at Beau-Bassin Prison, prisoners wanted to leave the prisons, the Special Supporting Unit (SSU) and Groupement d'Intervention de la Police Mauricienne (GIPM) had to intervene. Sixteen prison officers were injured.<ref name=\"Prison\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/agitations-la-prison-de-beau-bassin|title=Agitations \u00e0 la prison de Beau-Bassin|date=19 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320185836/https://defimedia.info/agitations-la-prison-de-beau-bassin|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Prison2\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-vinod-appadoo-enn-moman-donne-zot-inn-pran-kontrol-prizon|title=[Info Soir\u00e9e] : Vinod Appadoo : \"Enn moman donn\u00e9 zot inn pran kontrol prizon\"|date=19 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320161532/https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-vinod-appadoo-enn-moman-donne-zot-inn-pran-kontrol-prizon|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 20 March 2020, the Government of Mauritius announced that a Covid 19 Work Access Permit would be granted by the Monitoring Committee \u2013 Covid 19 to employers in specific sectors. This would allow their employees to move to their workplaces.<ref name=\"Eight\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-employes-autorises-se-rendre-au-travail-condition-davoir-un-covid-19-work-access-permit|title=Covid-19:les employ\u00e9s autoris\u00e9s \u00e0 se rendre au travail \u00e0 condition d'avoir un COVID-19 Work Access Permit|date=20 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322093137/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-employes-autorises-se-rendre-au-travail-condition-davoir-un-covid-19-work-access-permit|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"wrk\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-service-minimum-dans-les-services-essentiels-voici-un-communique-du-ministere-du-travail|title=Confinement total : service minimum dans les services essentiels, voici un communiqu\u00e9 du minist\u00e8re du Travail|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326191802/https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-service-minimum-dans-les-services-essentiels-voici-un-communique-du-ministere-du-travail|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 24 March 2020, the Prime Minister announced that the country would be under complete lock-down until 31 March 2020 with only essential services such as police, hospitals, dispensaries, private clinics, firefighters and banks being open. All other activities would be banned during the curfew period.<ref name=\"Edefs\">{{Cite web|url = https://ionnews.mu/video-covid-19-lockdown-renforce-supermarches-et-boulangeries-fermes-jusquau-31-mars-24032020/|title = &#91;Vid\u00e9o&#93; Covid-19 : Lockdown renforc\u00e9, supermarch\u00e9s et boulangeries ferm\u00e9s jusqu'au 31 mars|date = 24 March 2020|access-date = 26 March 2020|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200326090757/https://ionnews.mu/video-covid-19-lockdown-renforce-supermarches-et-boulangeries-fermes-jusquau-31-mars-24032020/|archive-date = 26 March 2020|url-status = live}}</ref> He also announced that all supermarkets, shops and bakeries would also be closed until 31 March 2020.<ref name=\"faf\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-de-3-cas-42-positifs-maurice|title=Covid-19 : De 3 cas \u00e0 42 positifs \u00e0 Maurice|date=24 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325205159/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-de-3-cas-42-positifs-maurice|archive-date=25 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"kli\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-le-ministre-yodiga-sawmynaden-face-la-presse-17h15|title=Confinement total : le ministre Yodiga Sawmynaden face \u00e0 la presse \u00e0 17h15|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326193417/https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-le-ministre-yodiga-sawmynaden-face-la-presse-17h15|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Following rumors on social media that a group of individuals were planning to attack supermarkets, the Special Mobile Force (SMF) quickly secured all major supermarkets around the island. A man posted on [[Facebook]] claiming that a supermarket and police station were already under attack, he later apologized and said that he had misinterpreted the information that he received. The man was arrested by the Central Criminal Investigation Department (CCID) on the same night for publishing fake news.<ref name=\"rio\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-interpelle-par-le-ccid|title=Fake news : Jahmeel Peerally interpell\u00e9 par le CCID|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326194716/https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-interpelle-par-le-ccid|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"riot\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-supprime-sa-publication-et-sexcuse|title=Fake News : Jahmeel Peerally supprime sa publication et s'excuse|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325202153/https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-supprime-sa-publication-et-sexcuse|archive-date=25 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 25 March 2020, the finance minister announced distribution of 35,000 food packs to families in the social register and those in need.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://ionnews.mu/video-padayachy-35-000-packs-de-vivres-seront-distribues-aux-demunis-25032020/|title = &#91;Vid\u00e9o&#93; Padayachy : 35 000 packs de vivres seront distribu\u00e9s aux d\u00e9munis|work = ION News|date = 25 March 2020|access-date = 26 March 2020|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200326090750/https://ionnews.mu/video-padayachy-35-000-packs-de-vivres-seront-distribues-aux-demunis-25032020/|archive-date = 26 March 2020|url-status = live}}</ref><ref name=\"solida\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/total-lockdown-la-distribution-de-vivres-debutera-le-jeudi-26-mars|title=Total lockdown : La distribution de vivres d\u00e9butera le jeudi 26 mars|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326193338/https://defimedia.info/total-lockdown-la-distribution-de-vivres-debutera-le-jeudi-26-mars|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A donation made by the founder of [[Alibaba Group]], [[Jack Ma]], arrived in Mauritius on that day. The cargo consisted of 20,000 Covid-19 screening kits, 100,000 masks and 1,000 protective suits for medical personnel. The [[African Union]] was responsible for ensuring that these supplies are delivered to the 54 African countries who benefited from this aid.<ref name=\"Alibaba\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/373353/covid-19-fournitures-medicales-offertes-jack-ma-sont|title=Covid-19: les fournitures m\u00e9dicales offertes par Jack Ma sont l\u00e0|date=25 March 2020|work=[[L'Express (Mauritius)]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On 26 March 2020, the government set up the Covid-19 Solidarity Fund, whose collected funds would be used to help people who have been affected by the pandemic.<ref name=\"fun\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-solidarity-fund-les-numeros-de-comptes-pour-apporter-votre-contribution|title=COVID-19 Solidarity Fund : Les num\u00e9ros de comptes pour apporter votre contribution|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327174955/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-solidarity-fund-les-numeros-de-comptes-pour-apporter-votre-contribution|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A mobile application named \"beSafeMoris\" was launched by the Ministry of Technology and Ministry of Health. The App provides latest news along with measures to prevent the proliferation of coronavirus.<ref name=\"besafe\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/besafemoris-une-application-gratuite-pour-des-informations-officielles-sur-le-covid-19|title=beSafeMoris : une application gratuite pour des informations officielles sur le Covid 19|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327210527/https://defimedia.info/besafemoris-une-application-gratuite-pour-des-informations-officielles-sur-le-covid-19|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The Deputy Commissioner of Police reported that 175 people had been charged for not respecting the curfew.<ref name=\"cur\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-la-sante-okenn-plas-pa-safe-0|title=[Info Soir\u00e9e] La Sant\u00e9 : \"Okenn plas pa safe\"|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327183859/https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-la-sante-okenn-plas-pa-safe-0|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Chief Commissioner of Rodrigues]], [[Serge Clair]] announced that all flights to Rodrigues island would be suspended until further notice.<ref name=\"rodrigues\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/le-chef-commissaire-serge-clair-annonce-la-suspension-des-vols-desservant-rodrigues|title=Le chef commissaire Serge Clair annonce la suspension des vols desservant Rodrigues|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327231818/https://defimedia.info/le-chef-commissaire-serge-clair-annonce-la-suspension-des-vols-desservant-rodrigues|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Supreme Court of Mauritius]] issued a communique to inform the public that all courts will be closed and Magistrates will be available through electronic devices for urgent matters such as request for bail, cancellation of arrest warrant and protection orders for children and victims of domestic violence.<ref name=\"sup\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-cours-de-justice-resteront-fermees-mais-des-magistrats-disponibles-par-voie-de-communication-technologique|title=Covid-19 : les cours de justice resteront ferm\u00e9es, mais des magistrats disponibles par voie de communication technologique|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327202439/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-cours-de-justice-resteront-fermees-mais-des-magistrats-disponibles-par-voie-de-communication-technologique|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"supreme\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-tribunaux-fermes-apres-la-contamination-dun-auxiliaire|title=Covid-19 : les tribunaux ferm\u00e9s apr\u00e8s la contamination d'un auxiliaire|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327232455/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-tribunaux-fermes-apres-la-contamination-dun-auxiliaire|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 30 March 2020, the Prime Minister, Mr Pravind Kumar Jugnauth, announced that the sanitary curfew which started on 23 March at 20 00 hours will be extended till 15 April 2020.<ref name=\"curfew\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-covid-19-le-couvre-feu-sanitaire-etendu-au-15-avril|title=[Info Soir\u00e9e] : COVID-19 : le couvre-feu sanitaire \u00e9tendu au 15 avril|date=30 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401030031/https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-covid-19-le-couvre-feu-sanitaire-etendu-au-15-avril|archive-date=1 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He also announced that supermarkets, excluding bakeries, would restart operations as from 2 April 2020. Customers will be allowed to enter supermarkets as per the alphabetical order of their names during specific days. It will be compulsory to bring their National Identity cards, wear masks and basic essential products would be limited to three units per person.<ref name=\"Sup\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/reouverture-des-supermarches-et-boutiques-voici-ce-quil-faut-retenir|title=R\u00e9ouverture des supermarch\u00e9s et boutiques : voici ce qu'il faut retenir|date=31 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\n* On 3 April 2020, the [[European Union]] contributed MUR 11.3 million to the Covid-2019 Solidarity Fund. As at 3 April 2020, MUR 28,025,759 had been collected.<ref name=\"mof2\">{{Cite news |url=http://mof.govmu.org/English//DOCUMENTS/COMMUNIQU%C3%89%20DE%20PRESSE%20CONJOINT%20-%20R%C3%89PUBLIQUE%20DE%20MAURICE%20ET%20UNION%20EUROP%C3%89ENE.PDF|title=Communiqu\u00e9 de presse R\u00e9publique de Maurice - Union europ\u00e9enne|date=3 April 2020 |work=Ministry of Finance, Economic Planning and Development|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"fund\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/lunion-europeenne-verse-rs-113-millions-dans-le-covid-19-solidarity-fund|title=L'Union europ\u00e9enne verse Rs 11,3 millions dans le Covid-19 Solidarity Fund|date=3 April 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 5 April 2020, the Minister of Foreign Affairs announced that 231 tonnes of equipment, including masks, overalls and other protective accessories for healthcare staff from [[Guangzhou]] and [[Beijing]] would be reaching Mauritius as from 10 April 2020.<ref name=\"equip\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/231-tonnes-de-materiel-de-protection-anti-covid-deux-vols-de-Chine-pour-le-10-avril-dit-bodha|title=231 tonnes de mat\u00e9riel de protection anti-Covid : \"Deux vols de Chine pour le 10 avril\", dit Bodha|date=5 April 2020|work= [[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 9 April 2020, the [[Mauritius Revenue Authority]] reported that out of 160,000 applications received for the Self Employed Scheme, more than 80,000 self-employed individuals already received MUR 5,100 and 11,000 employers benefited from the Wage Assistance Scheme.<ref name=\"9april\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/confinement-national-quelque-11-000-employeurs-ont-deja-beneficie-du-wage-assistance-scheme|title=Confinement national : quelque 11 000 employeurs ont d\u00e9j\u00e0 benefici\u00e9 du Wage Assistance Scheme|date=9 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref> The Mauritius Export Association (MEXA) reported that it members already produced 300,000 protective masks against the Covid-19.<ref name=\"Mexa\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-des-societes-se-lancent-dans-la-fabrication-de-masques-de-protection|title=Covid-19 : des soci\u00e9t\u00e9s se lancent dans la fabrication de masques de protection|date=9 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 9 April 2020, the Prime Minister, Pravind Kumar Jugnauth, during a videoconference from his residence, announced that the lockdown will be extended to Monday 04 May 2020, to further contain the spread of the Covid-19 in the country. With regard to Rodrigues and Agalega islands, the lockdown will end on 15 April 2020, barring the education sector.<ref name=\"govmuorg22\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.govmu.org/English/News/Pages/Covid-19-Lockdown-extended-to-04-May-2020,-announces-Prime-Minister.aspx|title=Covid-19: Lockdown extended to 04 May 2020, announces Prime Minister|date=10 April 2020|work=[[Government Portal of Mauritius]]}}</ref><ref name=\"lock\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-suivez-le-point-de-communication-du-gm-5|title=Covid-19 : suivez le point de communication du GM|date=10 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"lock2\">{{Cite news |url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-lepreuve-ne-finira-pas-de-sitot-dit-jugnauth-le-confinement-etendu-jusquau-4-mai-10042020/|title=Covid-19 : L'\u00e9preuve ne finira \"pas de sit\u00f4t\", dit Jugnauth ; le confinement \u00e9tendu jusqu'au 4 mai|date=10 April 2020|work=ION News|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 13 April 2020, IBL Ltd launched the COVID-19 HealthBot, it is a chatbot which allows users to know if they have symptoms of Covid-19.<ref name=\"IBL2\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/lancement-dune-interface-vous-aidant-savoir-si-vous-presentez-des-symptomes-du-covid-19ACTUALIT\u00c9S|title=Lancement d'une interface vous aidant \u00e0 savoir si vous pr\u00e9sentez des sympt\u00f4mes du Covid-19|date=13 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 15 April 2020, India sent 13 tonnes of medication and 500,000 [[Hydroxychloroquine]] tablets to Mauritius. Mauritius was among the first countries to receive supplies of this medicine after a special exemption was granted by India.<ref name=\"cloro\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-linde-sengage-contribuer-la-sante-publique-de-tous-les-mauriciens|title=Covid-19 : \" L'Inde s'engage \u00e0 contribuer \u00e0 la sant\u00e9 publique de tous les Mauriciens \"|date=15 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"cloro2\">{{Cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/hcq-india-emerges-first-responder-to-mauritius-seychelles-to-contain-covid-19/articleshow/75165108.cms|title=HCQ: India emerges first responder to Mauritius, Seychelles to contain Covid-19|date=15 April 2020|work=[[Economic Times]]}}</ref> On that day, a second donation of medical equipments from [[Jack Ma]] arrived in Mauritius.<ref name=\"jack\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/don-de-jack-ma-18-000-extraction-kits-recus-contre-le-covid-19-declare-janaki-sonoo|title=Don de Jack Ma : \" 18 000 Extraction kits \" re\u00e7us contre le Covid-19, d\u00e9clare Janaki Sonoo|date=15 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Cases==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Mauritius medical cases chart}}\n* The first patient was a 52-year-old man who had dual Belgian and Mauritian nationality. He returned to Mauritius from Belgium on 21 February 2020. He did not show any symptoms of the coronavirus upon his arrival. On 14 March 2020, he started to have fever and cough and was transferred to Victoria Hospital where the tests conducted on his lungs did not reveal anything suspicious. He showed no signs of fever,  with a body temperature of 36.6&nbsp;\u00b0C, and did not show any respiratory issues. The patient had diabetes. On 16 March 2020, the test did not show that he was infected by the coronavirus and he was put into isolation. On 17 March 2020, the second test was also negative, and on the same day, he started to have respiratory issues. The results of the third test showed that the patient was infected by the coronavirus. The patient died on 19 March 2020.<ref name=\"Nine\"/><ref name=\"fifteen\"/>\n* The second patient was a 59-year-old man who had both [[United Kingdom|British]] and [[Mauritius|Mauritian]] nationality. He came to attend the funeral of his brother in Mauritius on 7 March 2020 and had no symptoms upon arrival. At first, he visited a private doctor without revealing his travel history. It was when he was not feeling well that he went to a private clinic and revealed that he came from abroad. His health deteriorated and he was transferred to Victoria Hospital (Candos). He was then transported to Souillac Hospital. Following tests carried out on him, which turned out to be positive, he was placed in isolation at Souillac Hospital.<ref name=\"Second\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-trois-mauriciens-testes-positifs-zot-pe-gayn-tou-tretman-ki-bizin-rassure-le-pm|title=Covid-19 : trois Mauriciens test\u00e9s positifs ; \"zot pe gayn tou tretman ki bizin\", rassure le PM|date=19 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319191648/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-trois-mauriciens-testes-positifs-zot-pe-gayn-tou-tretman-ki-bizin-rassure-le-pm|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"dia\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/premier-deces-mauricien-lie-au-covid-19-steffy-sa-fille-ainee-mon-pere-etait-diabetique|title=Premier D\u00e9c\u00e8s Mauricien LI\u00e9 au covid-19 - Steffy, sa fille a\u00een\u00e9e : \"Mon p\u00e8re \u00e9tait diab\u00e9tique\"|date=23 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324175905/https://defimedia.info/premier-deces-mauricien-lie-au-covid-19-steffy-sa-fille-ainee-mon-pere-etait-diabetique|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* The third patient was a 21-year-old man who worked on a cruise ship. He came to Mauritius on 14 March 2020 and was placed under quarantine. He was later placed in isolation at Souillac Hospital.<ref name=\"Second\"/>\n* The fourth patient was a 25-year-old man who worked on a cruise ship. He came to Mauritius on 18 March 2020 and was placed under quarantine. He was later placed in isolation at Souillac Hospital.<ref name=\"Second\"/>\n* On 19 March 2020, the Prime Minister announced that four new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"Fifth\"/> The country reported its first death from coronavirus. The first 52-year-old patient died.<ref name=\"Eighth\">{{Cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-mauritius-idUKL8N2BE0AA|title=Mauritius says reports first death from coronavirus|date=21 March 2020|work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=21 March 2020|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321160132/https://uk.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-mauritius-idUKL8N2BE0AA|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Five new cases appeared in the country on 20 March 2020, raising the total number of  cases to 12.<ref name=\"Sixth\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-covid-19-12-cas-maurice|title=[Breaking News] Covid-19 : 12 cas \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|accessdate=21 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320172851/https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-covid-19-12-cas-maurice|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The five patients are the relatives of the second patient, they consist of three women aged 15, 40 and 56, and two men aged 52 and 67.<ref name=\"Seventh\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.vecret.com/blog/les-5-nouveaux-cas-lies-au-patient-zero-santaram-appa-voici-leurs-coordonnees.html|title=Les 5 nouveaux cas li\u00e9s au patient z\u00e9ro Santaram Appa: voici leurs coordonn\u00e9es|date=20 March 2020|work=Vecret|language=fr|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321051046/https://www.vecret.com/blog/les-5-nouveaux-cas-lies-au-patient-zero-santaram-appa-voici-leurs-coordonnees.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 21 March 2020, the Ministry of Health confirm that the number of cases rose to 14, of which nine cases were related to the second patient. One of the confirmed case of that day was a tourist from France, who isolated himself for two days while he was not feeling well and was treated for respiratory infection in a clinic in the north of the island.<ref name=\"fifteen\">{{Cite news|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-jagatpal-confirme-un-premier-deces-et-un-cas-dinfection-sur-un-francais-21032020/|title=[Vid\u00e9o] Covid-19 : Jagutpal confirme un premier d\u00e9c\u00e8s et un cas d'infection sur un Fran\u00e7ais|date=21 March 2020|work=ION NEWS|language=fr|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323183830/https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-jagatpal-confirme-un-premier-deces-et-un-cas-dinfection-sur-un-francais-21032020/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Nine\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/372956/deces-lie-au-coronavirus-gouvernement-confirme|title=D\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au coronavirus: le gouvernement confirme|date=21 March 2020|work=[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]]|language=fr|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321165032/https://www.lexpress.mu/article/372956/deces-lie-au-coronavirus-gouvernement-confirme|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Ten\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/news/covid-19-2e-jour-de-confinement-un-premier-deces-maurice-et-ce-quil-faut-retenir|title=Covid-19- 2e jour de confinement : un premier d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice et ce qu'il faut retenir|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=fr}}</ref> On the same day, it was reported that among the first cases reported in [[Madagascar]], one came from Mauritius and a second person from France transited through Mauritius before reaching Madagascar.<ref name=\"Mada\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/une-malgache-passee-par-maurice-testee-positive-madagascar|title=Une Malgache, pass\u00e9e par Maurice, test\u00e9e positive \u00e0 Madagascar|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=21 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203101/https://defimedia.info/une-malgache-passee-par-maurice-testee-positive-madagascar|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Mada2\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-3-cas-madagascar-parmi-les-personnes-infectees-une-jeune-de-19-ans-qui-est-revenue-de-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 3 cas \u00e0 Madagascar ; parmi les personnes infect\u00e9es une jeune de 19 ans qui est revenue de Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=20 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321174754/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-3-cas-madagascar-parmi-les-personnes-infectees-une-jeune-de-19-ans-qui-est-revenue-de-maurice|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 22 March 2020, 10 new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"Eleven\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-deuxieme-deces-maurice-24-cas-positifs-enregistres-jusquci|title=Covid-19 : quatre nouveaux cas enregistr\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322163054/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-deuxieme-deces-maurice-24-cas-positifs-enregistres-jusquci|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The second patient, aged 59, also died. It is estimated that he contaminated nine of his relatives and one doctor.<ref name=\"Zero\">{{Cite news|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-le-patient-zero-est-la-deuxieme-victime-du-coronavirus-22032020/|title=Covid-19 : Le patient z\u00e9ro est la deuxi\u00e8me victime du coronavirus|date=23 March 2020|work=ION NEWS|language=fr|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323183023/https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-le-patient-zero-est-la-deuxieme-victime-du-coronavirus-22032020/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Ne\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/373152/medecins-et-personnel-soignant-au-moins-un-cas-covid-19-confirme-deux-autres|title=M\u00e9decins et personnel soignant: au moins un cas de Covid-19 confirm\u00e9, deux autres suspect\u00e9s|date=23 March 2020|work=[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]]|language=fr|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324043335/https://www.lexpress.mu/article/373152/medecins-et-personnel-soignant-au-moins-un-cas-covid-19-confirme-deux-autres|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On the same day, four new cases were confirmed. The new cases confirmed on that day included four employees of a cruise ship, four who were related to the second patient, one traveler from Mumbai who reached Mauritius on 21 March 2020 and one who was a dentist.<ref name=\"Fifteen\">{{Cite news|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-28-cas-recenses-au-total-quatre-nouveaux-tests-positifs-sont-tombes-ce-soir-22032020/|title=Covid-19 : 28 cas r\u00e9cens\u00e9s au total, quatre nouveaux tests positifs sont tomb\u00e9s ce soir|date=22 March 2020|work=ION NEWS|language=fr|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323183023/https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-28-cas-recenses-au-total-quatre-nouveaux-tests-positifs-sont-tombes-ce-soir-22032020/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 23 March 2020, eight new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"Seventeen\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-36-cas-confirmes-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 36 cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice|date=23 March 2020|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=23 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323184725/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-36-cas-confirmes-maurice|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 26 March 2020, a huge spike of cases was reported, jumping from 48 to 81 cases in a single day.<ref name=\"agale\">{{Cite web|url=https://ionnews.mu/video-jugnauth-on-est-passe-de-48-a-81-cas-a-maurice-en-un-jour-26032020/|title=[Vid\u00e9o] Jugnauth : On est pass\u00e9 de 48 \u00e0 81 cas \u00e0 Maurice en un jour|date=26 March 2020|website=ION News|language=fr|access-date=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327105643/https://ionnews.mu/video-jugnauth-on-est-passe-de-48-a-81-cas-a-maurice-en-un-jour-26032020/|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On that day, a 20-year-old girl was tested positive. It has been claimed that she contracted the virus during a visit to a supermarket.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-nombre-de-cas-positifs-passe-52|title=Covid-19 : Le nombre de cas positifs passe \u00e0 52|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=26 March 2020|access-date=26 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326090753/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-nombre-de-cas-positifs-passe-52|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 27 March 2020, 13 new cases were reported, bringing the total to 43 imported cases and 51 locally transmitted.<ref name=\"27mar\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/suivi-de-la-pandemie-94-cas-positifs-au-covid-19-recenses-ce-jour|title=Suivi de la pand\u00e9mie : 94 cas positifs au Covid 19 recens\u00e9s \u00e0 ce jour|date=27 March 2020|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328180744/https://defimedia.info/suivi-de-la-pandemie-94-cas-positifs-au-covid-19-recenses-ce-jour|archive-date=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The total number of cases reached 94, including 57 men and 43 women.<ref name=\"woo\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-43-des-94-cas-recenses-maurice-sont-des-cas-importes|title=Covid-19 : 43 des 94 cas recens\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice sont des \"cas import\u00e9s\"|date=27 March 2020|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328181818/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-43-des-94-cas-recenses-maurice-sont-des-cas-importes|archive-date=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 28 March 2020, a man aged 76 was admitted to the hospital and died the same night. It has been reported that it was an imported case.<ref name=\"third\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/troisieme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-le-patient-hospitalise-dimanche-matin|title=Troisi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au Covid-19 : \" le patient hospitalis\u00e9 dimanche matin \"|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=30 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401020525/https://defimedia.info/troisieme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-le-patient-hospitalise-dimanche-matin|archive-date=1 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"third victim\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/coronavirus-un-quatrieme-deces-maurice|title=Coronavirus : Un quatri\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=31 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archiv