Access Permit|date=20 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322093137/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-employes-autorises-se-rendre-au-travail-condition-davoir-un-covid-19-work-access-permit|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"wrk\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-service-minimum-dans-les-services-essentiels-voici-un-communique-du-ministere-du-travail|title=Confinement total : service minimum dans les services essentiels, voici un communiqu\u00e9 du minist\u00e8re du Travail|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326191802/https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-service-minimum-dans-les-services-essentiels-voici-un-communique-du-ministere-du-travail|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 24 March 2020, the Prime Minister announced that the country would be under complete lock-down until 31 March 2020 with only essential services such as police, hospitals, dispensaries, private clinics, firefighters and banks being open. All other activities would be banned during the curfew period.<ref name=\"Edefs\">{{Cite web|url = https://ionnews.mu/video-covid-19-lockdown-renforce-supermarches-et-boulangeries-fermes-jusquau-31-mars-24032020/|title = &#91;Vid\u00e9o&#93; Covid-19 : Lockdown renforc\u00e9, supermarch\u00e9s et boulangeries ferm\u00e9s jusqu'au 31 mars|date = 24 March 2020|access-date = 26 March 2020|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200326090757/https://ionnews.mu/video-covid-19-lockdown-renforce-supermarches-et-boulangeries-fermes-jusquau-31-mars-24032020/|archive-date = 26 March 2020|url-status = live}}</ref> He also announced that all supermarkets, shops and bakeries would also be closed until 31 March 2020.<ref name=\"faf\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-de-3-cas-42-positifs-maurice|title=Covid-19 : De 3 cas \u00e0 42 positifs \u00e0 Maurice|date=24 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325205159/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-de-3-cas-42-positifs-maurice|archive-date=25 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"kli\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-le-ministre-yodiga-sawmynaden-face-la-presse-17h15|title=Confinement total : le ministre Yodiga Sawmynaden face \u00e0 la presse \u00e0 17h15|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326193417/https://defimedia.info/confinement-total-le-ministre-yodiga-sawmynaden-face-la-presse-17h15|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Following rumors on social media that a group of individuals were planning to attack supermarkets, the Special Mobile Force (SMF) quickly secured all major supermarkets around the island. A man posted on [[Facebook]] claiming that a supermarket and police station were already under attack, he later apologized and said that he had misinterpreted the information that he received. The man was arrested by the Central Criminal Investigation Department (CCID) on the same night for publishing fake news.<ref name=\"rio\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-interpelle-par-le-ccid|title=Fake news : Jahmeel Peerally interpell\u00e9 par le CCID|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326194716/https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-interpelle-par-le-ccid|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"riot\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-supprime-sa-publication-et-sexcuse|title=Fake News : Jahmeel Peerally supprime sa publication et s'excuse|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325202153/https://defimedia.info/fake-news-jahmeel-peerally-supprime-sa-publication-et-sexcuse|archive-date=25 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 25 March 2020, the finance minister announced distribution of 35,000 food packs to families in the social register and those in need.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://ionnews.mu/video-padayachy-35-000-packs-de-vivres-seront-distribues-aux-demunis-25032020/|title = &#91;Vid\u00e9o&#93; Padayachy : 35 000 packs de vivres seront distribu\u00e9s aux d\u00e9munis|work = ION News|date = 25 March 2020|access-date = 26 March 2020|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200326090750/https://ionnews.mu/video-padayachy-35-000-packs-de-vivres-seront-distribues-aux-demunis-25032020/|archive-date = 26 March 2020|url-status = live}}</ref><ref name=\"solida\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/total-lockdown-la-distribution-de-vivres-debutera-le-jeudi-26-mars|title=Total lockdown : La distribution de vivres d\u00e9butera le jeudi 26 mars|date=25 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326193338/https://defimedia.info/total-lockdown-la-distribution-de-vivres-debutera-le-jeudi-26-mars|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A donation made by the founder of [[Alibaba Group]], [[Jack Ma]], arrived in Mauritius on that day. The cargo consisted of 20,000 Covid-19 screening kits, 100,000 masks and 1,000 protective suits for medical personnel. The [[African Union]] was responsible for ensuring that these supplies are delivered to the 54 African countries who benefited from this aid.<ref name=\"Alibaba\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/373353/covid-19-fournitures-medicales-offertes-jack-ma-sont|title=Covid-19: les fournitures m\u00e9dicales offertes par Jack Ma sont l\u00e0|date=25 March 2020|work=[[L'Express (Mauritius)]]|language=fr|a