}</ref> The [[Chief Commissioner of Rodrigues]], [[Serge Clair]] announced that all flights to Rodrigues island would be suspended until further notice.<ref name=\"rodrigues\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/le-chef-commissaire-serge-clair-annonce-la-suspension-des-vols-desservant-rodrigues|title=Le chef commissaire Serge Clair annonce la suspension des vols desservant Rodrigues|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327231818/https://defimedia.info/le-chef-commissaire-serge-clair-annonce-la-suspension-des-vols-desservant-rodrigues|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Supreme Court of Mauritius]] issued a communique to inform the public that all courts will be closed and Magistrates will be available through electronic devices for urgent matters such as request for bail, cancellation of arrest warrant and protection orders for children and victims of domestic violence.<ref name=\"sup\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-cours-de-justice-resteront-fermees-mais-des-magistrats-disponibles-par-voie-de-communication-technologique|title=Covid-19 : les cours de justice resteront ferm\u00e9es, mais des magistrats disponibles par voie de communication technologique|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327202439/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-cours-de-justice-resteront-fermees-mais-des-magistrats-disponibles-par-voie-de-communication-technologique|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"supreme\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-tribunaux-fermes-apres-la-contamination-dun-auxiliaire|title=Covid-19 : les tribunaux ferm\u00e9s apr\u00e8s la contamination d'un auxiliaire|date=26 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327232455/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-les-tribunaux-fermes-apres-la-contamination-dun-auxiliaire|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 30 March 2020, the Prime Minister, Mr Pravind Kumar Jugnauth, announced that the sanitary curfew which started on 23 March at 20 00 hours will be extended till 15 April 2020.<ref name=\"curfew\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-covid-19-le-couvre-feu-sanitaire-etendu-au-15-avril|title=[Info Soir\u00e9e] : COVID-19 : le couvre-feu sanitaire \u00e9tendu au 15 avril|date=30 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401030031/https://defimedia.info/info-soiree-covid-19-le-couvre-feu-sanitaire-etendu-au-15-avril|archive-date=1 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He also announced that supermarkets, excluding bakeries, would restart operations as from 2 April 2020. Customers will be allowed to enter supermarkets as per the alphabetical order of their names during specific days. It will be compulsory to bring their National Identity cards, wear masks and basic essential products would be limited to three units per person.<ref name=\"Sup\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/reouverture-des-supermarches-et-boutiques-voici-ce-quil-faut-retenir|title=R\u00e9ouverture des supermarch\u00e9s et boutiques : voici ce qu'il faut retenir|date=31 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\n* On 3 April 2020, the [[European Union]] contributed MUR 11.3 million to the Covid-2019 Solidarity Fund. As at 3 April 2020, MUR 28,025,759 had been collected.<ref name=\"mof2\">{{Cite news |url=http://mof.govmu.org/English//DOCUMENTS/COMMUNIQU%C3%89%20DE%20PRESSE%20CONJOINT%20-%20R%C3%89PUBLIQUE%20DE%20MAURICE%20ET%20UNION%20EUROP%C3%89ENE.PDF|title=Communiqu\u00e9 de presse R\u00e9publique de Maurice - Union europ\u00e9enne|date=3 April 2020 |work=Ministry of Finance, Economic Planning and Development|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"fund\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/lunion-europeenne-verse-rs-113-millions-dans-le-covid-19-solidarity-fund|title=L'Union europ\u00e9enne verse Rs 11,3 millions dans le Covid-19 Solidarity Fund|date=3 April 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 5 April 2020, the Minister of Foreign Affairs announced that 231 tonnes of equipment, including masks, overalls and other protective accessories for healthcare staff from [[Guangzhou]] and [[Beijing]] would be reaching Mauritius as from 10 April 2020.<ref name=\"equip\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/231-tonnes-de-materiel-de-protection-anti-covid-deux-vols-de-Chine-pour-le-10-avril-dit-bodha|title=231 tonnes de mat\u00e9riel de protection anti-Covid : \"Deux vols de Chine pour le 10 avril\", dit Bodha|date=5 April 2020|work= [[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 9 April 2020, the [[Mauritius Revenue Authority]] reported that out of 160,000 applications received for the Self Employed Scheme, more than 80,000 self-employed individuals already received MUR 5,100 and 11,000 employers benefited from the Wage Assistance Scheme.<ref name=\"9april\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/confinement-national-quelque-11-000-employeurs-ont-deja-beneficie-du-wage-assistance-scheme|title=Confinement national : quelque 11 000 employeurs ont d\u00e9j\u00e0 benefici\u00e9 du Wage Assistance Scheme|date=9 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref> The Mauritius Export Association (MEXA) reported that it members already produced 300,000 protective masks against the Covid-19.<ref name=\"Mexa\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-des-societes-se-lancent-dans-la-fabrication-de-masques-de-protection|title=Covid-19 : des soci\u00e9t\u00e9s se lancent dans la fabrication de masques de protection|date=9 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 9 April 2020, the Prime Minister, Pravind Kumar Jugnauth, during a videoconference from his residence, announced that the lockdown will be extended to Monday 04 May 2020, to further contain the spread of the Covid-19 in the country. With regard to Rodrigues and Agalega islands, the lockdown will end on 15 April 2020, barring the education sector.<ref name=\"govmuorg22\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.govmu.org/English/News/Pages/Covid-19-Lockdown-extended-to-04-May-2020,-announces-Prime-Minister.aspx|title=Covid-19: Lockdown extended to 04 May 2020, announces Prime Minister|date=10 April 2020|work=[[Government Portal of Mauritius]]}}</ref><ref name=\"lock\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-suivez-le-point-de-communication-du-gm-5|title=Covid-19 : suivez le point de communication du GM|date=10 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"lock2\">{{Cite news |url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-lepreuve-ne-finira-pas-de-sitot-dit-jugnauth-le-confinement-etendu-jusquau-4-mai-10042020/|title=Covid-19 : L'\u00e9preuve ne finira \"pas de sit\u00f4t\", dit Jugnauth ; le confinement \u00e9tendu jusqu'au 4 mai|date=10 April 2020|work=ION News|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 13 April 2020, IBL Ltd launched the COVID-19 HealthBot, it is a chatbot which allows users to know if they have symptoms of Covid-19.<ref name=\"IBL2\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/lancement-dune-interface-vous-aidant-savoir-si-vous-presentez-des-symptomes-du-covid-19ACTUALIT\u00c9S|title=Lancement d'une interface vous aidant \u00e0 savoir si vous pr\u00e9sentez des sympt\u00f4mes du Covid-19|date=13 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n* On 15 April 2020, India sent 13 tonnes of medication and 500,000 [[Hydroxychloroquine]] tablets to Mauritius. Mauritius was among the first countries to receive supplies of this medicine after a special exemption was granted by India.<ref name=\"cloro\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-linde-sengage-contribuer-la-sante-publique-de-tous-les-mauriciens|title=Covid-19 : \" L'Inde s'engage \u00e0 contribuer \u00e0 la sant\u00e9 publique de tous les Mauriciens \"|date=15 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"cloro2\">{{Cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/hcq-india-emerges-first-responder-to-mauritius-seychelles-to-contain-covid-19/articleshow/75165108.cms|title=HCQ: India emerges first responder to Mauritius, Seychelles to contain Covid-19|date=15 April 2020|work=[[Economic Times]]}}</ref> On that day, a second donation of medical equipments from [[Jack Ma]] arrived in Mauritius.<ref name=\"jack\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/don-de-jack-ma-18-000-extraction-kits-recus-contre-le-covid-19-declare-janaki-sonoo|title=Don de Jack Ma : \" 18 000 Extraction kits \" re\u00e7us contre le Covid-19, d\u00e9clare Janaki Sonoo|date=15 April 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Cases==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Mauritius medical cases chart}}\n* The first patient was a 52-year-old man who had dual Belgian and Mauritian nationality. He returned to Mauritius from Belgium on 21 February 2020. He did not show any symptoms of the coronavirus upon his arrival. On 14 March 2020, he started to have fever and cough and was transferred to Victoria Hospital where the tests conducted on his lungs did not reveal anything suspicious. He showed no signs of fever,  with a body temperature of 36.6&nbsp;\u00b0C, and did not show any respiratory issues. The patient had diabetes. On 16 March 2020, the test did not show that he was infected by the coronavirus and he was put into isolation. On 17 March 2020, the second test was also negative, and on the same day, he started to have respiratory issues. The results of the third test showed that the patient was infected by the coronavirus. The patient died on 19 March 2020.<ref name=\"Nine\"/><ref name=\"fifteen\"/>\n* The second patient was a 59-year-old man who had both [[United Kingdom|British]] and [[Mauritius|Mauritian]] nationality. He came to attend the funeral of his brother in Mauritius on 7 March 2020 and had no symptoms upon arrival. At first, he visited a private doctor without revealing his travel history. It was when he was not feeling well that he went to a private clinic and revealed that he came from abroad. His health deteriorated and he was transferred to Victoria Hospital (Candos). He was then transported to Souillac Hospital. Following tests carried out on him, which turned out to be positive, he was placed in isolation at Souillac Hospital.<ref name=\"Second\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-trois-mauriciens-testes-positifs-zot-pe-gayn-tou-tretman-ki-bizin-rassure-le-pm|title=Covid-19 : trois Mauriciens test\u00e9s positifs ; \"zot pe gayn tou tretman ki bizin\", rassure le PM|date=19 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319191648/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-trois-mauriciens-testes-positifs-zot-pe-gayn-tou-tretman-ki-bizin-rassure-le-pm|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"dia\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/premier-deces-mauricien-lie-au-covid-19-steffy-sa-fille-ainee-mon-pere-etait-diabetique|title=Premier D\u00e9c\u00e8s Mauricien LI\u00e9 au covid-19 - Steffy, sa fille a\u00een\u00e9e : \"Mon p\u00e8re \u00e9tait diab\u00e9tique\"|date=23 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324175905/https://defimedia.info/premier-deces-mauricien-lie-au-covid-19-steffy-sa-fille-ainee-mon-pere-etait-diabetique|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* The third patient was a 21-year-old man who worked on a cruise ship. He came to Mauritius on 14 March 2020 and was placed under quarantine. He was later placed in isolation at Souillac Hospital.<ref name=\"Second\"/>\n* The fourth patient was a 25-year-old man who worked on a cruise ship. He came to Mauritius on 18 March 2020 and was placed under quarantine. He was later placed in isolation at Souillac Hospital.<ref name=\"Second\"/>\n* On 19 March 2020, the Prime Minister announced that four new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"Fifth\"/> The country reported its first death from coronavirus. The first 52-year-old patient died.<ref name=\"Eighth\">{{Cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-mauritius-idUKL8N2BE0AA|title=Mauritius says reports first death from coronavirus|date=21 March 2020|work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=21 March 2020|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321160132/https://uk.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-mauritius-idUKL8N2BE0AA|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Five new cases appeared in the country on 20 March 2020, raising the total number of  cases to 12.<ref name=\"Sixth\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-covid-19-12-cas-maurice|title=[Breaking News] Covid-19 : 12 cas \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|accessdate=21 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320172851/https://defimedia.info/breaking-news-covid-19-12-cas-maurice|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The five patients are the relatives of the second patient, they consist of three women aged 15, 40 and 56, and two men aged 52 and 67.<ref name=\"Seventh\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.vecret.com/blog/les-5-nouveaux-cas-lies-au-patient-zero-santaram-appa-voici-leurs-coordonnees.html|title=Les 5 nouveaux cas li\u00e9s au patient z\u00e9ro Santaram Appa: voici leurs coordonn\u00e9es|date=20 March 2020|work=Vecret|language=fr|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321051046/https://www.vecret.com/blog/les-5-nouveaux-cas-lies-au-patient-zero-santaram-appa-voici-leurs-coordonnees.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 21 March 2020, the Ministry of Health confirm that the number of cases rose to 14, of which nine cases were related to the second patient. One of the confirmed case of that day was a tourist from France, who isolated himself for two days while he was not feeling well and was treated for respiratory infection in a clinic in the north of the island.<ref name=\"fifteen\">{{Cite news|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-jagatpal-confirme-un-premier-deces-et-un-cas-dinfection-sur-un-francais-21032020/|title=[Vid\u00e9o] Covid-19 : Jagutpal confirme un premier d\u00e9c\u00e8s et un cas d'infection sur un Fran\u00e7ais|date=21 March 2020|work=ION NEWS|language=fr|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323183830/https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-jagatpal-confirme-un-premier-deces-et-un-cas-dinfection-sur-un-francais-21032020/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Nine\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/372956/deces-lie-au-coronavirus-gouvernement-confirme|title=D\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au coronavirus: le gouvernement confirme|date=21 March 2020|work=[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]]|language=fr|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321165032/https://www.lexpress.mu/article/372956/deces-lie-au-coronavirus-gouvernement-confirme|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Ten\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/news/covid-19-2e-jour-de-confinement-un-premier-deces-maurice-et-ce-quil-faut-retenir|title=Covid-19- 2e jour de confinement : un premier d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice et ce qu'il faut retenir|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=fr}}</ref> On the same day, it was reported that among the first cases reported in [[Madagascar]], one came from Mauritius and a second person from France transited through Mauritius before reaching Madagascar.<ref name=\"Mada\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/une-malgache-passee-par-maurice-testee-positive-madagascar|title=Une Malgache, pass\u00e9e par Maurice, test\u00e9e positive \u00e0 Madagascar|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=21 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203101/https://defimedia.info/une-malgache-passee-par-maurice-testee-positive-madagascar|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Mada2\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-3-cas-madagascar-parmi-les-personnes-infectees-une-jeune-de-19-ans-qui-est-revenue-de-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 3 cas \u00e0 Madagascar ; parmi les personnes infect\u00e9es une jeune de 19 ans qui est revenue de Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=20 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321174754/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-3-cas-madagascar-parmi-les-personnes-infectees-une-jeune-de-19-ans-qui-est-revenue-de-maurice|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 22 March 2020, 10 new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"Eleven\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-deuxieme-deces-maurice-24-cas-positifs-enregistres-jusquci|title=Covid-19 : quatre nouveaux cas enregistr\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322163054/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-deuxieme-deces-maurice-24-cas-positifs-enregistres-jusquci|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The second patient, aged 59, also died. It is estimated that he contaminated nine of his relatives and one doctor.<ref name=\"Zero\">{{Cite news|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-le-patient-zero-est-la-deuxieme-victime-du-coronavirus-22032020/|title=Covid-19 : Le patient z\u00e9ro est la deuxi\u00e8me victime du coronavirus|date=23 March 2020|work=ION NEWS|language=fr|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323183023/https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-le-patient-zero-est-la-deuxieme-victime-du-coronavirus-22032020/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Ne\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/373152/medecins-et-personnel-soignant-au-moins-un-cas-covid-19-confirme-deux-autres|title=M\u00e9decins et personnel soignant: au moins un cas de Covid-19 confirm\u00e9, deux autres suspect\u00e9s|date=23 March 2020|work=[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]]|language=fr|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324043335/https://www.lexpress.mu/article/373152/medecins-et-personnel-soignant-au-moins-un-cas-covid-19-confirme-deux-autres|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On the same day, four new cases were confirmed. The new cases confirmed on that day included four employees of a cruise ship, four who were related to the second patient, one traveler from Mumbai who reached Mauritius on 21 March 2020 and one who was a dentist.<ref name=\"Fifteen\">{{Cite news|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-28-cas-recenses-au-total-quatre-nouveaux-tests-positifs-sont-tombes-ce-soir-22032020/|title=Covid-19 : 28 cas r\u00e9cens\u00e9s au total, quatre nouveaux tests positifs sont tomb\u00e9s ce soir|date=22 March 2020|work=ION NEWS|language=fr|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323183023/https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-28-cas-recenses-au-total-quatre-nouveaux-tests-positifs-sont-tombes-ce-soir-22032020/|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 23 March 2020, eight new cases were confirmed.<ref name=\"Seventeen\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-36-cas-confirmes-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 36 cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice|date=23 March 2020|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|access-date=23 March 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323184725/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-36-cas-confirmes-maurice|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 26 March 2020, a huge spike of cases was reported, jumping from 48 to 81 cases in a single day.<ref name=\"agale\">{{Cite web|url=https://ionnews.mu/video-jugnauth-on-est-passe-de-48-a-81-cas-a-maurice-en-un-jour-26032020/|title=[Vid\u00e9o] Jugnauth : On est pass\u00e9 de 48 \u00e0 81 cas \u00e0 Maurice en un jour|date=26 March 2020|website=ION News|language=fr|access-date=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327105643/https://ionnews.mu/video-jugnauth-on-est-passe-de-48-a-81-cas-a-maurice-en-un-jour-26032020/|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On that day, a 20-year-old girl was tested positive. It has been claimed that she contracted the virus during a visit to a supermarket.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-nombre-de-cas-positifs-passe-52|title=Covid-19 : Le nombre de cas positifs passe \u00e0 52|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=26 March 2020|access-date=26 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326090753/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-nombre-de-cas-positifs-passe-52|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 27 March 2020, 13 new cases were reported, bringing the total to 43 imported cases and 51 locally transmitted.<ref name=\"27mar\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/suivi-de-la-pandemie-94-cas-positifs-au-covid-19-recenses-ce-jour|title=Suivi de la pand\u00e9mie : 94 cas positifs au Covid 19 recens\u00e9s \u00e0 ce jour|date=27 March 2020|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328180744/https://defimedia.info/suivi-de-la-pandemie-94-cas-positifs-au-covid-19-recenses-ce-jour|archive-date=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The total number of cases reached 94, including 57 men and 43 women.<ref name=\"woo\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-43-des-94-cas-recenses-maurice-sont-des-cas-importes|title=Covid-19 : 43 des 94 cas recens\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice sont des \"cas import\u00e9s\"|date=27 March 2020|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328181818/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-43-des-94-cas-recenses-maurice-sont-des-cas-importes|archive-date=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 28 March 2020, a man aged 76 was admitted to the hospital and died the same night. It has been reported that it was an imported case.<ref name=\"third\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/troisieme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-le-patient-hospitalise-dimanche-matin|title=Troisi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au Covid-19 : \" le patient hospitalis\u00e9 dimanche matin \"|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=30 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401020525/https://defimedia.info/troisieme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-le-patient-hospitalise-dimanche-matin|archive-date=1 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"third victim\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/coronavirus-un-quatrieme-deces-maurice|title=Coronavirus : Un quatri\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=31 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404120525/https://defimedia.info/coronavirus-un-quatrieme-deces-maurice|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"thi\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/coronavirus-un-troisieme-deces-maurice|title=Coronavirus : un troisi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=29 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401210001/https://defimedia.info/coronavirus-un-troisieme-deces-maurice|archive-date=1 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to Dr Vasant Rao Gujadhur who is the director of Health Services, on that day, eight new cases were confirmed, all of them were men aged between 40 and 86. On that day, Mauritius had 102 confirmed cases, including two deaths. Forty-four  were imported cases and 58 were locally transmitted. Seven hundred and fifty-six contact tracing tests were completed, 60 of them was tested positive.<ref name=\"pr\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-patient-sous-respiration-artificielle|title=COVID-19 : Un patient sous respiration artificielle|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=28 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329191951/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-patient-sous-respiration-artificielle|archive-date=29 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It was reported that three medical personnel were tested positive for the coronavirus in addition to four cases.<ref name=\"per\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-six-personnels-soignants-testes-positifs|title=COVID-19 : Six personnels soignants test\u00e9s positifs|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=28 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330183241/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-six-personnels-soignants-testes-positifs|archive-date=30 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 29 March 2020, five new cases were confirmed, four of whom were detected through contact tracing.<ref name=\"con\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-5-nouveaux-cas-positifs-maurice-107-au-total|title=COVID-19 : Quatre des cinq nouveaux cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9s par le contact tracing|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=29 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402183317/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-5-nouveaux-cas-positifs-maurice-107-au-total|archive-date=2 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"cn\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-quatre-des-cinq-nouveaux-cas-detectes-par-le-contact-tracing|title=Covid-19 : 5 nouveaux cas positifs \u00e0 Maurice ; 107 au total|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=29 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331050441/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-quatre-des-cinq-nouveaux-cas-detectes-par-le-contact-tracing|archive-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 30 March 2020, the Prime Minister [[Pravind Jugnauth]] confirmed that his test for coronavirus was negative.<ref name=\"Prav\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/teste-negatif-au-covid-19-cetait-tres-reconfortant-confie-pravind-jugnauth|title=Test\u00e9 n\u00e9gatif au Covid-19 : \" C'\u00e9tait tr\u00e8s r\u00e9confortant \", confie Pravind Jugnauth|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=30 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401023510/https://defimedia.info/teste-negatif-au-covid-19-cetait-tres-reconfortant-confie-pravind-jugnauth|archive-date=1 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> One of the confirmed cases on that day was an officer of the Passport and Immigration Office. He had arrived from Egypt one week earlier, was not placed under quarantine upon his arrival and had contact with several of his colleagues.<ref name=\"POI\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-officier-du-pio-teste-positif-apres-un-voyage-en-egypte|title=Covid-19 : un officier du PIO test\u00e9 positif apr\u00e8s un voyage en Egypte|date=30 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331183054/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-officier-du-pio-teste-positif-apres-un-voyage-en-egypte|archive-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* On 31 March 2020, two men aged 69 and 71 years old died.<ref name=\"twoman\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-5e-deces-maurice|title=Covid-19 : un 5e d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=31 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404120039/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-5e-deces-maurice|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* As at 1 April 2020, 1426 \u201ccontact tracing tests\u201d were completed. Among the infected people, 10 were under the age of 20, 59 people were between 49 and 59 and 26 were  60 years old or above.<ref name=\"dfg\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-6e-deces-maurice|title=COVID-19 : 6e d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=1 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404001455/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-6e-deces-maurice|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On that day, the 20 years old patient died, her family were unable to attend her funeral as they were also infected. It was reported that the family had to view her funeral through [[WhatsApp]].<ref name=\"des\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-7e-deces-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 7e d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=1 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"wat\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-infectes-ils-assistent-aux-funerailles-de-leur-fille-par-whatsapp|title=COVID-19 : Infect\u00e9s, ils assistent aux fun\u00e9railles de leur fille par WhatsApp|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=1 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404131333/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-infectes-ils-assistent-aux-funerailles-de-leur-fille-par-whatsapp|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* As at 2 April 2020, 1 703 people were under quarantine in different centers and hotels around the island.<ref name=\"rod\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/zouberr-joomaye-si-le-confinement-est-bien-respecte-maurice-natteindra-pas-le-pic-de-lepidemie|title=Zouberr Joomaye \" Si le confinement est bien respect\u00e9, Maurice n'atteindra pas le pic de l'\u00e9pid\u00e9mie \"|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=2 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404130934/https://defimedia.info/zouberr-joomaye-si-le-confinement-est-bien-respecte-maurice-natteindra-pas-le-pic-de-lepidemie|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Dr Vasantrao Gujadhur announced that eight children aged four months, two years, four, five, nine, 10, 12  and 15  were confirmed cases.<ref name=\"chil\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-bebe-de-4-mois-et-7-enfants-de-2-15-ans-touches|title=Covid-19 : Un b\u00e9b\u00e9 de 4 mois et 7 enfants de 2 \u00e0 15 ans touch\u00e9s|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=2 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404122316/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-bebe-de-4-mois-et-7-enfants-de-2-15-ans-touches|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On that day, a man aged 59 also died.<ref name=\"des\"/>\n* On 3 April 2020, the number of cases reached 186, 82 of which were imported cases and 104 locally transmitted.<ref name=\"Eighteenteen\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-17-nouveaux-cas-positifs-maurice-en-24-heures|title=Covid-19 : 17 nouveaux cas, 186 positifs \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=3 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> It was also confirmed that seven medical personnel were infected  as at 3 April 2020.<ref name=\"Twenty\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/sept-personnels-soignants-touches-par-le-coronavirus|title=Sept personnels soignants touch\u00e9s par le coronavirus|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=3 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* On 4 April 2020, the Prime Minister announced 10 new cases, and that seven patients were on the path to recovery; a second test will be conducted to confirm their recovery.<ref name=\"Recovery\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-sept-patients-sur-la-voie-de-la-guerison-selon-le-pm|title=Covid-19 : Sept patients sur la voie de la gu\u00e9rison selon le PM|date=4 April 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]] |language=fr |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On 5 April 2020, it was reported that 31 new cases were confirmed. Two patients were on artificial respirators. The total was 227, with 102 imported cases and 125 locally transmitted: 142 were men and 85 were women. There were 1,689 people under quarantine in 27 centers around the island.<ref name=\"5april\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-deux-patients-sous-respiration-artificielle-lhopital-ent|title=Covid-19 : deux patients sous respiration artificielle \u00e0 l'h\u00f4pital ENT|date=5 April 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]] |language=fr |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref> It was reported that 17 police officers including 12 officers of the Passport and Immigration Office were infected.<ref name=\"5april2\">{{Cite news |url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-17-policiers-testes-positifs|title=Covid-19 : 17 policiers test\u00e9s positifs|date=5 April 2020 |work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]] |language=fr |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On 6 April 2020, 17 new cases and the first four recoveries were confirmed.<ref name=\"6April\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-17-nouveaux-cas-positifs-244-cas-au-total|title=Covid-19 : 17 nouveaux cas positifs, 244 cas au total|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=6 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"Recovery2\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-quatre-patients-maurice-gueris|title=Covid-19 : quatre patients \u00e0 Maurice gu\u00e9ris|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=6 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> As at that date, the country had 244 positive cases, 133 through local transmission. Of these 133 cases, 94 were identified through contact tracing, and the remaining 39 were travellers who came from abroad but  were not in quarantine as they did not showed any symptoms related to Covid-19 on arrival. They developed the symptoms later and contributed to the local transmission.<ref name=\"6April2\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-39-cas-positifs-provenant-des-passagers-pas-places-en-quarantaine|title=Covid-19 : 39 cas positifs provenant des passagers pas plac\u00e9s en quarantaine|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=6 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* On 9 April 2020, 41 new cases and 12 recoveries was confirmed.<ref name=\"9April\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-41-nouveaux-cas-314-au-total-maurice|title=Covid-19 : 41 nouveaux cas, 314 au total \u00e0 Maurice|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=9 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"9April2\">{{Cite web|url=https://ionnews.mu/video-314-cas-de-covid-19-repertories-a-maurice-ce-9-avril-09042020/|title=[Vid\u00e9o] 314 cas de Covid 19 r\u00e9pertori\u00e9s \u00e0 Maurice ce 9 avril|website=ION NEWS|date=9 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> The minister of health had to put himself under isolation as one of his secretary was tested positive of the covid-19.<ref name=\"9April3\">{{Cite web|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-japatpal-sauto-isole-au-moins-cinq-employes-de-la-sante-testes-positifs-09042020/|title=Covid-19 : Jagutpal s'auto-isole, au moins cinq employ\u00e9s de la Sant\u00e9 test\u00e9s positifs|website=ION NEWS|date=9 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* On 10 April 2020, four new cases and two deaths were reported.<ref name=\"hiya\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-318-cas-positifs-maurice-9-deces|title=Covid-19 : 318 cas positifs \u00e0 Maurice, 9 d\u00e9c\u00e8s|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"Carl\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/le-fondateur-du-groupe-gamma-civic-decede-du-covid-19|title=Le fondateur du groupe Gamma Civic d\u00e9c\u00e8de du Covid-19|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> The members of the High Level Committee on Covid-19, including the Prime Minister Pravind Jugnauth, and those of the National Communication Committee started to self-isolate as they were in contact with the Minister of Health whose secretary was tested positive to the coronavirus.<ref name=\"9April6\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-premier-ministre-en-isolement|title=Covid-19 : Le Premier ministre en isolement|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> It was also reported that the second test made on the Director of Public Health Dr Vasantrao Gujadhur was negative, he isolated himself after one member of his contact tracing team was tested positive of the coronavirus.<ref name=\"10April8\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-deuxieme-test-negatif-pour-le-dr-gujadhur|title=Covid-19 : deuxi\u00e8me test n\u00e9gatif pour le Dr Gujadhur|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> Eight staffs of the Ministry of Health were also tested positive of the coronavirus.<ref name=\"9April8\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/huit-cas-positifs-de-covid-19-au-ministere-de-la-sante|title=Huit cas positifs de Covid-19 au minist\u00e8re de la Sant\u00e9\n|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=\"iuon\">{{Cite web|url=https://ionnews.mu/covid-19-le-prime-ministers-office-sauto-isole-et-work-from-home-10042020/|title=Covid-19 : Le Prime Minister's Office s'auto-isole et \"work from home\"|website=ION NEWS|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> 216 people who were under isolation and quarantined in Rodrigues island were tested negative of the coronavirus, they were allowed to return home.<ref name=\"rogds\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-confinement-leve-le-15-avril-rodrigues-et-agalega-sauf-dans-le-secteur-educatif|title=Covid-19 : le confinement lev\u00e9 le 15 avril \u00e0 Rodrigues et Agalega sauf dans le secteur \u00e9ducatif|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* One additional case was confirmed during the night of Friday 10 April. Five recoveries and no new cases were reported on 11 April 2020.<ref name=\"9April5\">{{Cite web|url=https://ionnews.mu/video-un-seul-cas-de-covid-19-detecte-entre-hier-et-ce-11-avril-319-cas-positifs-jusquici-11042020/|title=[Vid\u00e9o] Un seul cas de Covid-19 d\u00e9tect\u00e9 entre hier et ce 11 avril, 319 cas positifs jusqu'ici|website=ION NEWS|date=11 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* On 14 April 2020, no new cases were reported, the total number of cases was 324, including 51 recoveries and 9 death. The number of active cases was 261, three patients who were tested positive of the COVID-19 went back to their countries.<ref name=\"14April\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-aucun-positif-maurice-en-deux-jours|title=Covid-19 : aucun positif \u00e0 Maurice en deux jours|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=14 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* On 15 April 2020, no new cases were reported, the total number of cases was 324, including 65 recoveries and 9 death. The number of active cases was 247.<ref name=\"15April\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-le-nombre-de-patients-gueris-maurice-passe-65|title=Covid-19 : le nombre de patients gu\u00e9ris \u00e0 Maurice passe \u00e0 65|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=14 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref> Three patients who recovered from the coronavirus agreed to donate their blood through [[Plasmapheresis]].<ref name=\"plasma\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.inside.news/plasmapherese-3-patients-donnent-leur-accord-pour-un-don-de-sang/|title=Plasmaph\u00e9r\u00e8se: 3 patients donnent leur accord pour un don de sang|website=Inside News|date=15 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n* On 18 April 2020, one case was confirmed, 72 person recovered.<ref name=\"thre\"/>\n\n==Mauritians infected abroad==\n* A Mauritian woman, who works in [[Seychelles]], has tested positive for  Covid-19. According to reports, the woman contracted the virus through her spouse, who is a Ukrainian national. The couple work in a hotel. According to information communicated to the press by the Seychelles Commissioner for Public Health, the Ukrainian, who was on a trip, returned to Seychelles on 12 March 2020. It was then that he allegedly infected his spouse.<ref name=\"Third\">{{Cite news|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-une-mauricienne-testee-positive-aux-seychelles|title=Covid-19 : deuxi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Maurice, 24 cas positifs enregistr\u00e9s jusqu'ci|date=22 March 2020|work=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|language=fr|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319071043/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-une-mauricienne-testee-positive-aux-seychelles|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* It was reported that three Mauritians died from the coronavirus in France, including a 70-year-old doctor, who died on 22 March 2020, a second person  aged 83, who died on 29 March and a third person  aged 73 years old, who died on 31 March 2020.<ref name=\"France\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-troisieme-mauricien-meurt-en-france|title=Covid-19 : un troisi\u00e8me Mauricien meurt en France|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=1 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404144452/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-troisieme-mauricien-meurt-en-france|archive-date=4 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Fr\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/un-mauricien-meurt-du-covid-19-en-france-contamine-lhopital-alleguent-des-proches|title=Un Mauricien meurt du Covid-19 en France, contamin\u00e9 \u00e0 l'h\u00f4pital, all\u00e8guent des proches|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=30 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331200513/https://defimedia.info/un-mauricien-meurt-du-covid-19-en-france-contamine-lhopital-alleguent-des-proches|archive-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"doc\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-medecin-dorigine-mauricienne-meurt-en-france|title=Covid-19 : un m\u00e9decin d'origine mauricienne meurt en France|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=24 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325213758/https://defimedia.info/covid-19-un-medecin-dorigine-mauricienne-meurt-en-france|archive-date=25 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* It was reported that one Mauritian national was tested positive for the coronavirus in Ethiopia.<ref name=\"Ethopia\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/un-mauricien-atteint-du-covid-19-en-ethiopie|title=Un Mauricien atteint du Covid-19 en \u00c9thiopie|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=28 March 2020|language=fr|access-date=4 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329180528/https://defimedia.info/un-mauricien-atteint-du-covid-19-en-ethiopie|archive-date=29 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* On 5 April 2020, the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Nando Bodha reported that 46 Mauritians who work on the cruise ship Costa Luminosa were unable to land in [[Marseille|Marseilles]],  because the French authorities did not authorize disembarcation. They were then directed to [[Savona]], [[Italy]], where it was established that six of them were infected. The latter underwent treatments in health centers. The remaining 40 were taken to Rome and placed in a quarantined hotel.<ref name=\"costa\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/mauriciens-coinces-par-le-confinement-generalise-les-compagnies-de-croisiere-ont-toutes-un-billet-retour-dit-bodha|title=Mauriciens coinc\u00e9s par le confinement g\u00e9n\u00e9ralis\u00e9 : \"Les compagnies de croisi\u00e8re ont toutes un billet retour\", dit Bodha|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=5 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* On 10 April 2020, it was reported that a Mauritian doctor was tested positive in Switzerland.<ref name=\"swit\">{{Cite web|url=https://defimedia.info/teste-positif-au-covid-19-un-medecin-suisse-dorigine-mauricienne-autorise-rentrer-chez-lui|title=Test\u00e9 positif au Covid-19 : un m\u00e9decin suisse d'origine mauricienne autoris\u00e9 \u00e0 rentrer chez lui|website=[[Le D\u00e9fi Media Group]]|date=10 April 2020|language=fr|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> \n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:right; font-size:90%;\"\n|+\nConfirmed cases of Mauritian nationals abroad\n!Country/Region\n!Confirmed cases\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Flugzeugtr\u00e4ger_Silhouette.svg|23x15px|alt=|link=]] Costa Luminosa\n|6\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|France}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]]\n|3\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|Seychelles}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Seychelles|Seychelles]]\n|1\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|Ethiopia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ethiopia|Ethiopia]]\n|1\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|Switzerland}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Switzerland|Switzerland]]\n|1\n|-\n!Total\n!12\n|}\n\n== Charts based on daily reports ==\nCharts based on daily reports from the Mauritian Ministry of Health on confirmed cases of Covid-19.<ref name=\"9Aprl4\">{{Cite web|url=https://besafemoris.mu/stats/|title=Mauritius Statistics|website=Besafemoris|date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"MRUStats\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/mauritius/|title=Mauritius Statistics|website=Worldometer|date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type= line\n|linewidth= 1\n|showSymbols= 1\n|width= 680\n|colors= #FF6347,#FFC000,#87CEEB,#000000\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle= Date of daily report\n|xAxisAngle= -40\n|x= 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 